–1180":"1125–1180","1135–1180":"1135–1180","1110–Female":"1110–Deceased","Abt 1135":"about 1135","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1110":"1110","about 1125":"about 1125","1180":"1180","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Scotland, United Kingdom","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Drummond","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places, notably the barony of Drummond, which is probably identical with the parish of Drymen (Stirlingshire), named from Gaelic <i>drumainn</i>, a derivative of <i>druim</i> ‘ridge’. It has been said that the principal family of this name are descended from a Hungarian nobleman, Maurice, who accompanied Edgar Atheling and his sister Margaret to Scotland in 1068, where she married King Malcolm III. However, there is disagreement on whether or not this was the case.","English: occasionally perhaps from an unrecorded Middle English personal name <i>Dromund</i> (Old Norse <i>Drómundr</i>, apparently from a word denoting a kind of Byzantine galley prevalent till the 12th cent., from Greek <i>dromōn</i> ‘runner’)."],"variants":[{"name":"Drummonds","meanings":["Scottish: variant of   Drummond  , with post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>. In Britain this surname is found mainly in County Durham."]}]},{"name":"Maurice","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From the Late Latin name <i>Mauricius</i>, a derivative of <i>Maurus</i> (a byname meaning ‘Moor’, i.e. ‘dark, swarthy’), borne by, among others, an early Byzantine emperor (  <i>c.</i>539–602 ). It was introduced to Britain by the Normans and was popular in the Middle English period, but was not widely adopted by the nobility and became rare in the 17th century. Between the mid-19th century and the 1940s, it was moderately popular but has since faded again.  See also  Morris ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Mrs. Maurice Drummond was born in 1110, in Stirlingshire, Scotland, United Kingdom. She had at least 2 sons with Maurice Drummond 3rd Thane of Lennox. She died in Scotland, United Kingdom."},"et":{"1110–":"1110–Surnud","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1125–1180":"1125–1180","1135–1180":"1135–1180","1110–Female":"1110–Surnud","Abt 1135":"umbes 1135","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1110":"1110","about 1125":"umbes 1125","1180":"1180","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Scotland":"Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1110–":"1110–Kuollut","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1125–1180":"1125–1180","1135–1180":"1135–1180","1110–Female":"1110–Kuollut","Abt 1135":"noin 1135","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1110":"1110","about 1125":"noin 1125","1180":"1180","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Scotland":"Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1110–":"1110–Décédée","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1125–1180":"1125–1180","1135–1180":"1135–1180","1110–Female":"1110–Décédée","Abt 1135":"environ 1135","1125":"1125","1135":"1135","1155":"1155","1100":"1100","1110":"1110","about 1125":"environ 1125","1180":"1180","Drymen, Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Drymen, Stirlingshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Scotland":"Écosse, Royaume-Uni","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Mrs. Maurice Drummond est née en 1110, à Stirlingshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 2 fils avec Maurice Drummond 3rd Thane of Lennox. Elle est décédée à Écosse, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"1110–":"1110–Verstorben","1100–1155":"1100–1155","1125–1180":"1125–1180"